description: Plates 21-22 (double-page); Car drawn by a camel; 2 organs-- the "positive" played by Master Paul Hofhaimer, court organist at Innsbruck, "best remembered for his metrical setting for odes of Horace...important precursors of the Protestant hymn style and homophonoc developments in music."
